					<h2 id="wylie">Who Was Turrell Wylie?</h2>
					<p>Turrell Verl "Terry" Wylie (August 20, 1927 – August 25, 1984) was a prominent American scholar, Tibetologist, sinologist, and professor. He is widely recognized as one of the leading Western experts on Tibetan language, culture, and history in the 20th century.</p>

					<p>He developed a system of Roman script to write down Tibetan language. This was highly necessary some time ago to enable publishing Tibetan texts, before the invention of Unicode. Now, we don't need to use Wylie as much as we did in the past; but some academics, especially in Europe, insist on continuous use of Wylie in academic publications instead of Tibetan script.</p>

